cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the communication protocol for short-range cellular-V2X (C-V2X) in vehicular networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of PHY and MAC parameters on the system performance, which involves the analysis of information transmission and processing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the allocation of resources in a distributed system, which requires control and optimization techniques. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the exchange of information between vehicles and roadside devices, which may involve multimedia data such as video or audio. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon the security aspects of C-V2X communication, although it is not explicitly mentioned in the abstract.
